div2.entryFree:

      أَطْبَخُ Confirmed in stupidity; as also ↓ طَبْخَةٌ;
(L, K;) but the word commonly known is
طَيْخَةٌ. (L.)


      4 
      اطحّهُ He made it to fall, threw it down, or
let it fall: and he threw it. (Fr, O, K.)


      2 
      طلّف عَلَيْهِ, inf. n. تَطْلِيفٌ; (O, K;) and
ظلّف is a dial. var. thereof; (TA;) He exceeded
it; (O, K;) [meaning a certain number of years;
for] it is like ذَرَّفَ and رَمَّثَ and طَلَّثَ. (IAar,
TA in art. ظلف.)


      طَمِمٌ Hardy, strong, or sturdy: occurring thus,
without idghám, in a verse of 'Adee Ibn-Zeyd;
applied to a beast such as is termed قَارِحٌ. (TA.)


      مُطَيَّحٌ, accord. to the K, signifies Bad,
corrupt, or vitious: but it may be a mistransscription, for مُطَبَّحٌ [or this is a mistranscription
for مُطَيَّخٌ, which is expl. as having this meaning]. (TA.)
